const headHtml = "<title>Best Mining Money-Making Methods in Hypixel SkyBlock</title>\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"An expert based 2026 mining guide comparing accessible routes, powder-heavy setups, gear breakpoints and how to choose between casual mining and endgame capital sinks.\">\n    <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/mining-money-making-guide-2026\">\n\n    <meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/mining-money-making-guide-2026\">\n    <meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\">\n    <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"Best Mining Money-Making Methods in Hypixel SkyBlock\">\n    <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Use current creator walkthroughs to separate casual mining routes from heavy-investment late-game mining.\">\n    <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/static/NEC.png\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\n        \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n        \"@type\": \"BlogPosting\",\n        \"headline\": \"Best Mining Money-Making Methods in Hypixel SkyBlock\",\n        \"description\": \"Expert based guide to the strongest mining money methods in Hypixel SkyBlock.\",\n        \"datePublished\": \"2026-02-02\",\n        \"dateModified\": \"2026-04-18\",\n        \"author\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"NotEnoughCoins\"},\n        \"publisher\": {\"@type\": \"Organization\", \"name\": \"Coflnet GmbH\"},\n        \"url\": \"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/mining-money-making-guide-2026\"\n      }\n    </script>";
const bodyHtml = "<main>\n      <div class=\"site-shell article-layout\">\n        <article class=\"article\">\n          <a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-02-02 • Mining</a>\n          <h1>Best Mining Money-Making Methods in Hypixel SkyBlock</h1>\n          <p class=\"lede\">Mining is one of the most misunderstood money paths in SkyBlock because creators often showcase it from completely different account states. One video is aimed at players with almost no powder, another assumes expensive drills and pristine gear, and a third compares routes that only make sense if your ping, route control and hotm perks are already strong. The result is a lot of confusion that disappears once you separate accessible mining from heavily capitalized mining.</p>\n\n          <div class=\"note\">\n            <strong>Primary source base:</strong> Xentyl's 2026 test of easy mining methods, FarmerWarden's mining-start guide and broader method-comparison coverage from 2025 route videos.\n          </div>\n\n          <h2>Not every mining guide is talking to the same player</h2>\n          <p>The most useful thing in the current mining coverage is not the headline number; it is the way the methods divide naturally by setup cost. Casual diamond, coal or simpler route mining can still be relevant because it asks far less of your account. Those methods may not compete with polished gemstone setups at the top end, but they are much easier to reach and far less punishing if your powder, pet and gear are still incomplete.</p>\n          <p>That is where many players get trapped. They watch an endgame mining video, hear a giant coins-per-hour claim and assume mining as a category is impossible without a full late-game kit. The better guides do not make that mistake. They show that there is a real middle layer: routes that already generate respectable money before you have perfect gemstones, giant powder pools or the most expensive drill upgrades on the market.</p>\n\n          <h2>Gear breakpoints change the answer</h2>\n          <p>Mining is unusually sensitive to gear breakpoints. A method can be technically profitable at low setup and still feel weak compared with the effort required. Once routes become dependent on the pristine stat, mining spread, powder allocation or forge timing, the experience changes from a simple farm into a full optimization project. That is why later pages in this series split gemstone mining and sludge mining out from this overview instead of flattening everything together.</p>\n          <p>You should read this overview as a sorting page. If you want straightforward entry routes, stay with simpler ore and route methods until the account is ready. If you already have the budget for Divan pieces, stronger drills and meaningful powder allocation, the specialized mining pages will be more useful. The mistake is trying to copy the last stage of mining before the account can actually support it.</p>\n\n          <h2>Route quality and competition still decide your real income</h2>\n          <p>Mining money is not just a spreadsheet problem. It depends on whether your route is clean, whether another player is stripping the same nodes, whether your movement is stable and whether you are converting supporting materials efficiently afterward. This is why route guides keep mattering. A mining method with a slightly lower theoretical ceiling but cleaner execution can outperform a fancier setup you cannot pilot consistently.</p>\n          <p>Use the live tools to check the value of what your route actually produces. <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/topMovers\">SkyCofl top movers</a> catches mining-output swings in real time, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/forge\">SkyCofl forge flips</a> shows whether forge layering still beats raw selling, <a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/\">Skyblock.bz</a> ranks mining products by 24h movement, <a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/craft-forge-flips\">BazaarPro craft &amp; forge flips</a> exposes compactor and converter edges, and <a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/margin\">BazaarTracker margin</a> sanity-checks spread depth. A route that felt average last week can improve quickly once the supporting drops become more liquid.</p>\n\n          <h2>Choose the branch that matches your account</h2>\n          <p>If you are evaluating mining honestly, ask three questions first. How much powder do you already have? How much capital can you actually lock into gear? And do you want a route you can run casually, or are you ready to manage forge layers and optimization rules? Once those answers are clear, the mining tree becomes much easier to read.</p>\n\n          <h2>Read next</h2>\n          <ul class=\"related-list\">\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/slayer-money-making-guide-2026\">Best Slayer Money-Making Methods in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/gemstone-mining-guide\">Gemstone Mining Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/sludge-mining-guide\">Sludge Mining Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n\n        <aside class=\"article-aside\">\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best paired tools</h3>\n            <ul class=\"tool-list\">\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/topMovers\">SkyCofl top movers</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/forge\">SkyCofl forge flips</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://skyblock.bz/\">Skyblock.bz trends</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/craft-forge-flips\">BazaarPro craft &amp; forge flips</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/converters\">BazaarPro converters</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://bazaartracker.com/margin\">BazaarTracker margin</a></li>\n            </ul>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best for</h3>\n            <p>Players deciding whether mining is ready to become a main income stream or should stay a later progression target.</p>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Source videos</h3>\n            <p>Xentyl and FarmerWarden help frame the split between accessible mining and capital-heavy optimization.</p>\n          </div>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n    </main>";
